# ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │  tsseg-exp  —  Environment Configuration                             │
# │                                                                      │
# │  Copy this file to .env and fill in the values for your setup.       │
# │  The .env file is loaded automatically by the experiment pipeline.   │
# │  It is .gitignored — never commit secrets.                           │
# └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

# ── Conda ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the conda executable (only needed if conda is not in PATH).
# CONDA=/path/to/miniconda3/bin/conda

# ── Cluster profile ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Switch between cluster accounts by setting CLUSTER_PROFILE.
# Each profile is a separate .env.<name> file with cluster-specific
# settings (CLUSTER_USER, CLUSTER_HOST, CLUSTER_WORKDIR, etc.).
#
# To add a new profile, create .env.<name> with at least:
#   CLUSTER_USER, CLUSTER_HOST, CLUSTER_WORKDIR, TSSEG_MLFLOW_DIR
#
# CLUSTER_PROFILE=cleps

# ── Workspace ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each workspace is an isolated environment with its own:
#   - mlflow.db          SQLite database
#   - mlartifacts/       Run artifacts
#   - outputs/           Hydra outputs
#   - multirun/          Hydra multirun sweeps
#
# Workspaces live under workspaces/<origin>/<name>/:
#   - workspaces/local/<name>/    for locally-created workspaces
#   - workspaces/cluster/<name>/  for workspaces pulled from the cluster
#
# Format: <origin>/<name>   (e.g. local/main, local/dev, cluster/main)
# A bare name like "main" is treated as "local/main".
#
# TSSEG_WORKSPACE=local/main

# ── MLflow Tracking ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# How experiment results are stored.  Two modes are supported:
#
#   MODE 1 — Local SQLite database (default, zero config)
#     The workspace's mlflow.db is used automatically.
#     MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=sqlite:///workspaces/local/main/mlflow.db
#
#   MODE 2 — Remote MLflow server (recommended for cluster work)
#     Point to a running MLflow Tracking Server (see scripts/README.md).
#     MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=http://<hostname>:15050
#
# Uncomment ONE of the lines below:
# MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=sqlite:///workspaces/local/main/mlflow.db
# MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=http://clusterXXXX:15050

# ── Cluster connection ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# SSH host used by run_experiments.sh and submit_mlflow to reach the
# SLURM cluster.  Defaults shown below — override only if needed.
# These are typically set by the cluster profile (.env.<name>) rather
# than here.
#
# CLUSTER_HOST=cluster-login-node
# CLUSTER_USER=$USER

# ── MLflow auto-discovery (cluster) ──────────────────────────────────
#
# When using a remote MLflow server started via SLURM (see scripts/),
# the server hostname is dynamic.  Set TSSEG_MLFLOW_DIR to the shared
# directory where the server writes its connection file.  The scripts
# will SSH to CLUSTER_HOST and read
#   <TSSEG_MLFLOW_DIR>/workspaces/<name>/mlflow_node.txt
# to discover the URI — but ONLY if MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI is not set.
# Note: only the workspace <name> part is used on the remote side
# (the origin prefix local/ or cluster/ is stripped).
#
# TSSEG_MLFLOW_DIR=/scratch/<user>/tsseg-exp
